The Long Lartin Prison in the West Midlands, England, is a Category C men's prison. It is the largest prison in the United Kingdom and the largest in Europe. It is located in the village of Long Lartin, near Evesham, Worcestershire.
The prison was built in 1993 and is operated by the private company G4S. It is the only prison in the United Kingdom to have a fully automated system for the delivery of food to prisoners.
The prison is home to the largest number of foreign national prisoners in the United Kingdom.
The prison is also home to the largest number of prisoners serving life sentences in the United Kingdom.

The Macedonian government has decided to change the country’s name to North Macedonia, in order to end a decades-long dispute with Greece.
The name change was approved by the Macedonian parliament on Tuesday, with 80 votes in favour and 15 against.
The decision was made after the government reached a deal with Greece in June, which will see the country renamed the Republic of North Macedonia.
The deal was agreed after Greece dropped its objections to the name change, which had been a major stumbling block in the country’s bid to join the European Union and NATO.
The deal was signed by the two countries’ foreign ministers in the presence of EU foreign policy chief Federica Mogherini.

Wikidata: Ronaldo
Ronaldo (Portuguese pronunciation: [ɾɔˈnɔlɔ]; born 5 February 1985) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays as a forward for Spanish club Real Madrid and the Portugal national team. He is widely regarded as one of the greatest footballers of all time.
Ronaldo is the all-time top scorer in the history of the UEFA Champions League with 120 goals, and is the only

Spanish: <s>Gran Premio de Rusia: Lewis Hamilton se acerca al título mundial después de que las órdenes del equipo le entregaran la victoria sobre Sebastian Vettel</s>
Catalan: <s>Gran Premi de Rusia: Lewis Hamilton se aproxima al título mundial después de que el equipo le entregara la victoria sobre Sebastian Vettel</s>
The 2018 Russian Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race held on 27 October 2018 at the Sochi Autodrom in Sochi, Russia. It was the thirteenth round of the 2018 Formula One World Championship.
The race was won by Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes, his sixth victory of the season and his 65th career victory. It was also his 50th career win for Mercedes.
The race was the first Russian Grand Prix since 2014, and the first to be held in the country since 1985.
The race was won by Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes, his sixth victory of the season and his 65th career victory. It was also his 50th career win for Mercedes.
The race was the first Russian Grand Prix since 2014, and the first to be held in the country since 1985.

The Ryder Cup is a biennial golf competition between teams from Europe and the United States. The competition is named after Samuel Ryder, a British businessman who founded the competition in 1927.
The Ryder Cup is played every two years, alternating between the United States and Europe. The competition is played over three days, with each day consisting of four four-ball matches and four foursomes matches. The team with the most points at the end of the competition is declared the winner.
The Ryder Cup is one of the most prestigious golf competitions in the world. It is also one of the most watched sporting events in the world, with millions of people tuning in to watch the action.
